{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17595031","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17595031"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:58:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:58:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15329"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15329","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15329"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.19,0,0,0.81]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8020"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69325"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8020","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8020"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15329"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54778"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8755"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19489"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19491"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69325","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/69325"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EBridging fibrosis is an important histological finding that indicates progression of chronic liver disease. It is characterised by bands of collagen deposition that connect different anatomical structures within the liver.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following conditions most commonly causes bridging fibrosis in the liver?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hepatic adenoma","Acute alcoholic hepatitis","Gilbert syndrome","Simple hepatic steatosis","Chronic viral hepatitis"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChronic viral hepatitis\u003C/strong\u003E commonly leads to bridging fibrosis through persistent inflammation and subsequent collagen deposition. These fibrous bands typically form between portal tracts (portal-portal bridging) or between portal tracts and central veins (portal-central bridging).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAcute alcoholic hepatitis\u003C/strong\u003E causes acute inflammation and hepatocyte ballooning but does not immediately result in bridging fibrosis\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESimple hepatic steatosis\u003C/strong\u003E involves fat accumulation within hepatocytes without significant fibrosis formation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGilbert syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is a benign inherited condition affecting bilirubin metabolism that does not cause liver damage\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatic adenoma\u003C/strong\u003E is a benign liver tumour that does not cause diffuse liver fibrosis\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBridging fibrosis represents an intermediate stage of liver damage between chronic inflammation and cirrhosis. Its presence indicates progressive liver disease that may eventually lead to cirrhosis if the underlying cause is not addressed.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Bridging fibrosis in the liver represents bands of fibrosis extending between portal tracts or between portal tracts and central veins","Chronic viral hepatitis is a common cause of bridging fibrosis in the liver","Bridging fibrosis is a precursor to cirrhosis and indicates progressive liver damage"],"references":["Joseph A, Samant H. Jaundice. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31334972","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Gasmi B, Kleiner DE. Liver Histology: Diagnostic and Prognostic Features. Clin Liver Dis. 2020 Feb;24(1):61-74. doi: 10.1016/j.cld.2019.09.004. Epub 2019 Oct 31. PMID: 31753251; PMCID: PMC6986808","Mehta P, Grant LM, Reddivari AKR. Viral Hepatitis. 2024 Mar 10. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32119436."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54778"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15329"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54778","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/54778"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-11T19:42:20+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-11T19:44:16+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8020"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69325"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/